[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 1 — __init__ now sets _day_idx=-1 and calls
  self.reset() at the end of __init__ so _day_bars is populated before SB3 ever
  touches the env. Without this, the first step() saw _day_bars=None and returned
  truncated=True immediately, giving ep_len=1.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 1 — step() guard replaced: removed the silent
  reset()-and-return that masked bad state. Now uses assert _day_bars is not None
  and returns zero-obs with truncated=True on normal end-of-day overflow.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 2 — Capital compounding added in step():
  self._capital += trade_pnl - trade_cost, floored at 1000, _max_capital tracked,
  self._gr.capital synced. Capital was previously static so model never saw
  account growth/decline in its reward signal.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 3 — debug_env() function added before
  run_sac_training(). Runs 200 random-action steps, prints per-episode
  len/reward/trades, raises RuntimeError if mean ep_len < 10. Training is blocked
  until the environment is healthy.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 3 — run_sac_training() now builds raw env,
  calls debug_env(), then wraps in Monitor instead of building wrapped env directly.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: BUG 4 — _apply_position() captures check_entry()
  reason (was discarding with _) and prints "Entry blocked: {reason}" for diagnosis.

[2026-05-24] guardrails.py :: ROOT CAUSE FIX — reset_day() now resets
  self.realized_pnl = 0.0. Previously realized_pnl accumulated across days;
  on episode 2 step 1, update_unrealised() saw the full prior-day loss, fired
  daily_halted=True, and every episode after ep 1 terminated on step 1.

[2026-05-24] guardrails.py :: reset_day() also resets pos_n50=0.0 and
  pos_nbank=0.0 explicitly as a safety belt (HG8 force-exit should clear these,
  but belt-and-suspenders against stale state).

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: DEAD_BAND raised 0.05 → 0.15 → 0.20.
  SAC's uniform-random init spread across [-1,1]; larger dead-band zeroes out
  noise trades during early training before the policy has learned anything.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _bars_since_entry_n50 / _bars_since_entry_nbank
  counters added to __init__ and reset() (both reset to 0), incremented in step()
  after bar_idx advance. Counter resets to 0 when position is flat.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _apply_position() — minimum hold period:
  initially MIN_HOLD_BARS=3 (flip-only), then strengthened to MIN_HOLD_BARS=6
  blocking ANY change while in a position (not just direction flips). This stopped
  the 33-45 trades/70-bar pattern from random action flipping.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _apply_position() — lots fixed at 1.
  Old formula max(1, round(pos_frac * capital / (close * lot_size))) gave 1 lot
  but that's ₹16.5L notional on ₹50k capital = 33× leverage. Fixed to lots=1
  at all 4 calculation sites (_apply_position, _check_stop_losses × 2,
  _force_exit × 2, _unrealised_pnl × 2).

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: P&L formula fixed at all exit sites.
  Old: pos_fraction * price_move * lot_size * lots / abs(pos_fraction)
  — this mixed allocation fraction with lot count, effectively multiplying
  lot_size twice. New formula: direction * price_move * lot_size * lots
  where direction = 1 if long else -1. Fixed in _apply_position,
  _check_stop_losses (N50 + NBANK), _force_exit (N50 + NBANK), _unrealised_pnl.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: HG3 single-trade loss cap added at every exit:
  pnl = max(pnl, -(self._capital * 0.02)). Applied in _apply_position,
  _check_stop_losses (both instruments). Not applied to _force_exit (EOD P&L
  is what it is; capping would distort account tracking).

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — two asserts added:
  capital in (0, 10M) and abs(trade_pnl) < capital*2. These crash loud if
  the capital or P&L state becomes nonsensical rather than silently training
  on garbage reward values.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — pnl_pct clipped to ±10%
  per bar. Before this fix, raw rupee P&L was producing rewards of -14000,
  which caused SAC's critic to diverge.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — catastrophic-loss penalty
  reduced 100 → 10 (it sits inside the ±20 clip anyway; -100 was saturating
  the critic). Final reward clip tightened from [-200, 200] to [-20, 20].

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: Overtrading penalty tightened:
  threshold 10 → 4 trades/day, multiplier 2 → 5 per excess trade.
  4 trades/day is generous for an intraday system; strong penalty needed to
  discourage random flipping during early exploration.

