[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — core P&L signal rescaled.
  pnl_pct (range ±10) divided by 10 → pnl_scaled (range ±1) before applying
  asymmetry multiplier. Old code used raw pnl_pct producing per-bar rewards of
  ±10 before any penalties, which dominated and destabilised the critic.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — all penalty/bonus magnitudes
  recalibrated so every component fits inside [-3, +3] total:
    catastrophic loss penalty:  10   → 5.0
    overtrading multiplier:      5   → 1.0  (per trade above threshold 4)
    time-window violation:      50   → 3.0
    regime alignment bonus:      1.0 → 0.1
    exposure concentration:     *10  → *1.0
    drawdown scaling:           *2   → *0.2

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — survival bonus added:
  +0.01 per bar when both positions are flat. Gives SAC a weak signal that
  "do nothing" is a valid baseline, without overwhelming the P&L signal.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: _compute_reward() — final clip tightened:
  [-20, 20] → [-3, 3]. Target: good trading day ≈ +0.5 to +2.0 total episode
  reward; bad day ≈ -1.0 to -3.0. SAC critic learns best with rewards in ~[-5,+5].

