[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: SAC_KWARGS — learning_rate 3e-4 → 1e-4.
  Critic loss was oscillating between 1.5e5 and 8.5e5. Smaller LR reduces
  gradient step size, letting the critic converge more smoothly.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: SAC_KWARGS — learning_starts 5_000 → 10_000.
  More random exploration before learning starts gives the replay buffer
  a richer distribution of (s, a, r, s') transitions before gradient updates begin.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: SAC_KWARGS — batch_size 256 → 512.
  Larger minibatches produce lower-variance gradient estimates, reducing
  the critic update noise that was driving the loss spikes.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: SAC_KWARGS — policy_kwargs now includes
  optimizer_kwargs=dict(eps=1e-5). Adam's epsilon controls the denominator
  floor; 1e-5 (vs default 1e-8) dampens large gradient updates on noisy
  reward signals, acting as implicit gradient clipping.

[2026-05-24] sac_trainer.py :: TOTAL_TIMESTEPS 500_000 → 1_000_000.
  Complex environment (50 features, 2 outputs, guardrail masking) needs
  1-2M steps for the critic to stabilise and the actor to find profitable
  patterns. 500k was insufficient.

