[2026-05-27] sac_trainer.py :: CHANGE 1 — VecNormalize + DummyVecEnv removed entirely.
  train_env is now Monitor(train_env_raw); val_env is a raw NiftyTradingEnv.
  Removed: DummyVecEnv/VecNormalize imports, both VecNormalize wrap blocks,
  vecnormalize.pkl save line, stale unwrap logic in MetricsCallback._run_eval().
  VecNormalize's running-reward normalisation was creating a gap between what SAC
  optimised (normalised) and what Sharpe measures (raw ₹ returns).

[2026-05-27] sac_trainer.py :: CHANGE 2 — _compute_reward() rewritten with ATR normalisation.
  Old: pnl_pct / 10 → [-1,+1] then asymmetric multipliers + structural penalties.
  New: pnl_pts = net_pnl / 75 (lot-point units), then r = pnl_pts / (daily_atr * 0.1)
  clipped to [-3,+3]. Capturing 10% of daily ATR = reward +1.0.
  Regime-direction penalties ±0.2 kept; catastrophic/overtrading penalties removed.
  Reward is now regime-independent and in a natural [-3,+3] range without external normalisation.

[2026-05-27] sac_trainer.py :: CHANGE 3 — Entropy target + initial ent_coef fixed.
  target_entropy -0.5 → -1.0 (more negative forces more exploration).
  Added ent_coef='auto_0.5' so SAC starts entropy coefficient at 0.5 and auto-tunes
  down, rather than starting near 0 and collapsing immediately.

[2026-05-27] sac_trainer.py :: CHANGE 4 — learning_starts 10_000 → 20_000.
  Model was updating before the replay buffer had enough diverse (s,a,r,s') transitions;
  early bad gradient estimates caused critic divergence before useful patterns could form.

